					<shape type="circle" radius="18"/>
					<of>STA_driven_government_consumption</of>
				</alias>
				<alias font_style="italic" uid="405" x="275.895" y="1177.89" width="18" height="18">
					<of>Paid_Total_Nominal_SLR_protection_cost</of>
				</alias>
				<alias color="black" background="#00F900" font_style="italic" font_weight="bold" font_color="black" uid="449" x="2987.74" y="1537.84" width="18" height="18">
					<of>government_insurance_policy_start_year</of>
				</alias>
			</view>
		</views>
	</model>
	<model name="Inflation">
		<variables>
			<stock name="Inflation Index" access="output" isee:autocreated="true">
				<doc>Inflation index (often called a price index or CPI index) is a cumulative measure of how much price have changed over time. 
E.g., if the inflation index = 1.2, the price today is 20% higher than in the base year.

“What is the overall price level today compared to the base year?”

it is used to compute the real GDP</doc>
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>initial_inflation_index</eqn>
				<inflow>change_in_inflation_index</inflow>
				<units>dmnl</units>
			</stock>
			<flow name="change in\ninflation index">
				<doc>The inflation index increases at a rate equal to the inflation rate times the current index.

Inflation changes the current price level, not the base year price level. Inflation is exponential (compounding), not linear.</doc>
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>Inflation_Rate*Inflation_Index

{IF TIME &gt; 2020 THEN inflation_percentage ELSE 0,1-RAMP(,002; STARTTIME)</eqn>
				<units>1/year</units>
			</flow>
			<aux name="aggregate\nincome">
				<doc>It is the total income available to the whole economy (all sectors combined).
It includes income generated and paid by the private sector AND net injections or withdrawals from the government sector</doc>
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>private_income+net_government_expenses</eqn>
				<units>b$/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="net\ngovernment\nexpenses">
				<doc>Net government expenses represent the government’s net injection or withdrawal of money into the private economy. When it spends → it injects income.
When it taxes → it withdraws income
When it provides bailouts → it injects additional income

If government_spending &gt; tax_income
→ government is injecting money → aggregate income rises.</doc>
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>public_expenditure-total_public_tax_income_1 +bailouts</eqn>
				<units>b$/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="income\ngrowth rate">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>INFLATION_IMPACT_GROWTH_RATE(aggregate_income, 1, initial_income_growth_rate)</eqn>
				<units>1/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="initial\nincome\ngrowth rate">
				<doc>${Internal Calibration Parameter}
</doc>
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>0.020044647</eqn>
				<range min="0" max="0.1"/>
				<units>1/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="wages 1" access="input">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>{Enter equation for use when not hooked up to other models}</eqn>
				<units>b$/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="total public tax income 1" access="input">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>{Enter equation for use when not hooked up to other models}</eqn>
				<units>b$/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="public\nexpenditure" access="input">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>{Enter equation for use when not hooked up to other models}</eqn>
				<units>b$/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="bank profits" access="input">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>{Enter equation for use when not hooked up to other models}</eqn>
				<units>B$/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="non bank profits" access="input">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>{Enter equation for use when not hooked up to other models}</eqn>
				<units>b$/year</units>
			</aux>
			<stock name="Inflation Rate" access="output" isee:autocreated="true">
				<doc>Inflation rate is the percentage change in prices per year.
If it is &gt; 0, then the prices are rising. If it is &lt; 0, the prices are falling (deflation).

“How fast are prices increasing right now?”</doc>
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>initial_inflation_rate</eqn>
				<inflow>inflationary_pressure</inflow>
				<outflow>deflationary_pressure</outflow>
				<units>1/year</units>
			</stock>
			<flow name="inflationary\npressure">
				<doc>If the inflation gap is positive, inflation must rise.
The rise is gradual, over the inflation_adjustment_time.
Only positive gaps create inflationary pressure.

The MAX(0, …) ensures equation does not treat a negative gap as “negative pressure”; that is handled separately.</doc>
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>MAX(0, inflation_gap/inflation_adjustment_time)</eqn>
				<non_negative/>
				<units>1/year/Year</units>
			</flow>
			<aux name="inflation\nadjustment time">
				<doc>${Assumption,Internal Calibration Parameter}
</doc>
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<element subscript="1">
					<eqn>1.45058032478617</eqn>
				</element>
				<range min="0.25" max="1.5"/>
				<units>year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="private\nincome">
				<doc>All private income flows come from three sources: wages or salary, profits (non-bank profits received by firm and bank profits received by financial sector), rent (owned by owners).
</doc>
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>non_bank_profits
+ bank_profits
+ wages_1
+ rent</eqn>
				<units>b$/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="crop production" access="input">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>{Enter equation for use when not hooked up to other models}</eqn>
				<units>PCal/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="animal products demand" access="input">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>{Enter equation for use when not hooked up to other models}</eqn>
				<units>PCal/Year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="crop demand" access="input">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>{Enter equation for use when not hooked up to other models}</eqn>
				<units>PCal/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="crop supply\ngrowth rate">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>INFLATION_IMPACT_GROWTH_RATE(crop_production, 1, initial_crop_supply_growth_rate)</eqn>
				<units>dmnl/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="initial crop supply\ngrowth rate">
				<doc>${Internal Calibration Parameter}
</doc>
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>0.02</eqn>
				<range min="0" max="0.1"/>
				<units>dmnl/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="crop demand\ngrowth rate">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>INFLATION_IMPACT_GROWTH_RATE(crop_demand, 1, initial_crop_demand_growth_rate)</eqn>
				<units>dmnl/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="initial crop\ndemand\ngrowth rate">
				<doc>${Internal Calibration Parameter}
</doc>
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>0.02</eqn>
				<range min="0" max="0.1"/>
				<units>dmnl/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="crop market\nbalance">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>crop_demand_growth_rate-crop_supply_growth_rate</eqn>
				<units>dmnl/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="agriculture\ninflation\ncontribution">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>(crop_market_balance+animal_products_market_balance)*agriculture_share_of_GDP</eqn>
				<units>dmnl/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="animal products production" access="input">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>{Enter equation for use when not hooked up to other models}</eqn>
				<units>PCal/Year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="animal products\nproduction growth rate">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>INFLATION_IMPACT_GROWTH_RATE(animal_products_production, 1, initial_animal_products_production_growth_rate)</eqn>
				<units>dmnl/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="initial animal\nproducts production\ngrowth rate">
				<doc>${Internal Calibration Parameter}
</doc>
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>0.035</eqn>
				<range min="0" max="0.1"/>
				<units>dmnl/Year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="animal products\ndemand growth rate">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>INFLATION_IMPACT_GROWTH_RATE(animal_products_demand, 1, initial_animal_products_demand_growth_rate)</eqn>
				<units>dmnl/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="initial animal\nproducts demand\ngrowth rate">
				<doc>${Internal Calibration Parameter}
</doc>
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>0.02</eqn>
				<range min="0" max="0.1"/>
				<units>dmnl/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="animal products\nmarket balance">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>animal_products_demand_growth_rate-animal_products_production_growth_rate</eqn>
				<units>dmnl/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="agriculture percentage of GDP">
				<doc>${Calibrated Output}
</doc>
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>MAX(0, 
agriculture_share_of_GDP_starting_point_determinant*EXP(agriculture_share_of_GDP_slope*relative_change_in_GDP_per_person)+Agriculture_share_of_GDP_intercept)</eqn>
				<units>dmnl</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="Agriculture share\nof GDP\nintercept">
				<doc>${Internal Calibration Parameter}
</doc>
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<element subscript="1">
					<eqn>3.44861681058744</eqn>
				</element>
				<range min="0" max="100"/>
				<units>dmnl</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="agriculture share\nof GDP slope">
				<doc>${Internal Calibration Parameter}
</doc>
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<element subscript="1">
					<eqn>-2.28814519206221</eqn>
				</element>
				<range min="-10" max="1"/>
				<units>Million*Person*Years/b$</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="agriculture share\nof GDP starting point determinant">
				<doc>${Internal Calibration Parameter}
</doc>
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<element subscript="1">
					<eqn>19.8770195984429</eqn>
				</element>
				<range min="0" max="20"/>
				<units>dmnl</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="relative change\nin GDP per person">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>real_GDP_per_person/INIT(real_GDP_per_person)</eqn>
				<units>dmnl</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="agriculture\nshare of GDP">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>agriculture_percentage_of_GDP/100</eqn>
				<units>dmnl</units>
			</aux>
			<stock name="Employed" access="input">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>{Enter equation for use when not hooked up to other models}</eqn>
				<non_negative/>
				<units>Mp</units>
			</stock>
			<aux name="employment\ngrowth">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>INFLATION_IMPACT_GROWTH_RATE(Employed, 1, initial_employed_growth)</eqn>
				<units>dmnl/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="initial employed growth">
				<doc>${Internal Calibration Parameter}
</doc>
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>-0.014951251</eqn>
				<range min="-0.05" max="0.05"/>
				<units>dmnl/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="realised productivity" access="input">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>{Enter equation for use when not hooked up to other models}</eqn>
				<units>dmnl</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="employment and\nproductivity growth">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>productivity_growth_1 + employment_growth</eqn>
				<units>dmnl/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="indicated\ninflation rate">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>income_growth_rate-employment_and_productivity_growth</eqn>
				<units>1/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="rent" access="input">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>{Enter equation for use when not hooked up to other models}</eqn>
				<units>b$/year</units>
			</aux>
			<flow name="deflationary\npressure">
				<doc>If the inflation gap is negative, inflation should fall.
This negative adjustment happens gradually.
Only negative gaps trigger deflation.

MIN(0, …) isolates the negative part. The negative sign makes the outflow positive.</doc>
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>-MIN(0, inflation_gap/deflation_adjustment_time)</eqn>
				<non_negative/>
				<units>dmnl/year^2</units>
			</flow>
			<aux name="inflation gap">
				<doc>Inflation gap is the difference between:
(1) what inflation should be, based on cost pressures and economic factors
(2) the current inflation rate.

This gap tells whether inflation needs to go up or down.
If gap &gt; 0 → inflation should rise.
If gap &lt; 0 → inflation should fall.</doc>
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>indicated_inflation_rate
+agriculture_inflation_contribution
+marginal_energy_cost_inflation_contribution
+cropland_inflation_contribution
+grazing_land_inflation_contribution
+fertilizer_used_per_unit_of_crop_production_inflation_contribution
+irrigation_water_used_per_unit_of_crop_production_inflation_contribution
-Inflation_Rate</eqn>
				<units>1/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="deflation\nadjustment time">
				<doc>${Internal Calibration Parameter}
</doc>
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<element subscript="1">
					<eqn>3.82527832406061</eqn>
				</element>
				<range min="2.5" max="10"/>
				<units>years</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="productivity\ngrowth 1" access="input">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>{Enter equation for use when not hooked up to other models}</eqn>
				<units>dmnl/Year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="time to measure growth rate">
				<doc>${Internal Calibration Parameter}
</doc>
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>2</eqn>
				<range min="1.5" max="2.5"/>
				<units>year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="marginal energy cost\ninflation contribution">
				<doc>Energy scarcity or abundance directly increases or decreases inflation scaled by a weight parameter.

If the energy market is tight (positive balance), Energy prices rise, higher energy prices make production more expensive, inflation increases</doc>
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>energy_market_balance*weight_of_marginal_energy_cost_inflation</eqn>
				<units>dmnl/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="weight of marginal energy\ncost inflation">
				<doc>${Internal Calibration Parameter}
</doc>
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<element subscript="1">
					<eqn>0.812232845424</eqn>
				</element>
				<range min="0.01" max="2"/>
				<units>dmnl</units>
			</aux>
			<stock name="Cropland" access="input">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>{Enter equation for use when not hooked up to other models}</eqn>
				<units>Mha</units>
			</stock>
			<aux name="growth rate in cropland">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>INFLATION_IMPACT_GROWTH_RATE(Cropland, time_to_measure_growth_rate, initial_growth_rate_in_cropland)</eqn>
				<units>dmnl/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="cropland inflation contribution">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>growth_rate_in_cropland*weight_of_cropland_inflation_contribution</eqn>
				<units>dmnl/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="weight of cropland inflation contribution">
				<doc>${Internal Calibration Parameter}
</doc>
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<element subscript="1">
					<eqn>0.0944956053433003</eqn>
				</element>
				<range min="0.001" max="2"/>
				<units>dmnl</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="initial growth rate\nin cropland">
				<doc>${Internal Calibration Parameter}
</doc>
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>0.00275</eqn>
				<range min="0" max="0.1"/>
				<units>1/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="fertilizer used per\nunit of crop production" access="input">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>{Enter equation for use when not hooked up to other models}</eqn>
				<units>Million*tN/PCal</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="growth rate in fertilizer used\nper unit of crop production">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>INFLATION_IMPACT_GROWTH_RATE(fertilizer_used_per_unit_of_crop_production, time_to_measure_growth_rate)</eqn>
				<units>1/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="fertilizer used\nper unit of crop production\ninflation contribution">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>growth_rate_in_fertilizer_used_per_unit_of_crop_production*weight_of_fertilizer_used_per_unit_of_crop_production</eqn>
				<units>dmnl/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="weight of fertilizer used per unit of crop production">
				<doc>${Internal Calibration Parameter}
</doc>
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<element subscript="1">
					<eqn>0.0178717567090785</eqn>
				</element>
				<range min="0.001" max="2"/>
				<units>dmnl</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="grazing land" access="input">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>{Enter equation for use when not hooked up to other models}</eqn>
				<units>Mha</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="growth rate in grazing land">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>INFLATION_IMPACT_GROWTH_RATE(grazing_land, time_to_measure_growth_rate, initial_growth_rate_in_grazing_land)</eqn>
				<units>dmnl/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="grazing land inflation contribution">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>growth_rate_in_grazing_land*weight_of_grazing_land_inflation_contribution</eqn>
				<units>dmnl/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="weight of grazing land inflation contribution">
				<doc>${Internal Calibration Parameter}
</doc>
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<element subscript="1">
					<eqn>0.0543838689604846</eqn>
				</element>
				<range min="0.001" max="2"/>
				<units>dmnl</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="initial growth rate in grazing land">
				<doc>${Internal Calibration Parameter}
</doc>
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>0.001</eqn>
				<range min="0" max="0.1"/>
				<units>1/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="irrigation water used\nper unit of crop production" access="input">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>{Enter equation for use when not hooked up to other models}</eqn>
				<units>Million^3/PCal</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="growth rate in irrigation water used per unit of crop production">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>INFLATION_IMPACT_GROWTH_RATE(irrigation_water_used_per_unit_of_crop_production, time_to_measure_growth_rate)</eqn>
				<units>dmnl/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="irrigation water used per unit of crop production inflation contribution">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>growth_rate_in_irrigation_water_used_per_unit_of_crop_production*weight_of_irrigation_water_used_per_unit_of_crop_production_inflation_contribution</eqn>
				<units>dmnl/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="weight of irrigation water used per unit of crop production inflation contribution">
				<doc>${Internal Calibration Parameter}
</doc>
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<element subscript="1">
					<eqn>0.0501917669680645</eqn>
				</element>
				<range min="0.001" max="2"/>
				<units>dmnl</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="initial inflation index">
				<doc>${Internal Calibration Parameter}
</doc>
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<element subscript="1">
					<eqn>0.382993181667638</eqn>
				</element>
				<range min="0.35" max="0.55"/>
				<units>dmnl</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="initial inflation rate">
				<doc>${Internal Calibration Parameter}
</doc>
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<element subscript="1">
					<eqn>0.0613770977264824</eqn>
				</element>
				<range min="0" max="0.1"/>
				<units>1/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="real GDP per person" access="input">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>{Enter equation for use when not hooked up to other models}</eqn>
				<units>bc$/Mp/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="Real GDP in 2021c$" access="input">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>{Enter equation for use when not hooked up to other models}</eqn>
				<units>bc$/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="Nominal GDP" access="input">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>{Enter equation for use when not hooked up to other models}</eqn>
				<units>b$/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="real GDP per person 1" access="input">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>{Enter equation for use when not hooked up to other models}</eqn>
				<units>bc$/Mp/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="inflation adjustment b$ per bc$" access="output" isee:autocreated="true">
				<doc>“How many nominal dollars correspond to one constant 2021 dollar?”

Inflation Index = the cumulative price level relative to the base year (2021).
unit_b$_per_bc$ = a unit-conversion constant (1 nominal B$ per 1 constant bc$ in the base year).

If Inflation Index = 1.30 → inflation adjustment = 1.30 nominal B$ per 1 bc$.</doc>
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>Inflation_Index*&quot;unit_b$_per_bc$&quot;</eqn>
				<units>b$/bc$</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="unit b$ per bc$">
				<doc>${Unit}
a unit-conversion constant (1 nominal B$ per 1 constant bc$ in the base year).</doc>
				<eqn>1</eqn>
				<units>b$/bc$</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="inflation adjustment $ per c$" access="output" isee:autocreated="true">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>&quot;unit_$_per_c$&quot;*Inflation_Index</eqn>
				<units>$/c$</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="unit $ per c$">
				<doc>${Unit}
</doc>
				<eqn>1</eqn>
				<units>$/c$</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="bailouts" access="input">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>{Enter equation for use when not hooked up to other models}</eqn>
				<units>b$/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="Inflation Rate as Percent">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>Inflation_Rate*UNIT_Percent</eqn>
				<units>%/Years</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="UNIT Percent" access="output" isee:autocreated="true">
				<doc>${Unit}
</doc>
				<eqn>100</eqn>
				<units>%</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="gdp difference">
				<doc>${Calibrated Output}
</doc>
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>Nominal_GDP-&quot;Real_GDP_in_2021c$&quot;*unit_fixer</eqn>
				<units>b$/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="unit fixer">
				<doc>${Unit}
</doc>
				<eqn>1</eqn>
				<units>b$/bc$</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="demand for energy" access="input">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>{Enter equation for use when not hooked up to other models}</eqn>
				<units>TWh/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="Total Energy Output" access="input">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>{Enter equation for use when not hooked up to other models}</eqn>
				<units>TWh/Year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="energy supply\ngrowth rate">
				<doc>The equation computes the smoothed annual growth rate of total energy output. It tells you how fast energy supply is increasing or decreasing, averaged over one year.

Using INFLATION_IMPACT_GROWTH_RATE allows FRIDA to capture the trend growth of energy supply, not the noisy point-to-point change.</doc>
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>INFLATION_IMPACT_GROWTH_RATE(Total_Energy_Output, 1, initial_energy_supply_growth_rate)</eqn>
				<units>dmnl/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="initial energy supply\ngrowth rate">
				<doc>${Internal Calibration Parameter}
</doc>
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>0.02</eqn>
				<range min="0" max="0.1"/>
				<units>dmnl/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="energy demand\ngrowth rate">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>INFLATION_IMPACT_GROWTH_RATE(demand_for_energy, 1, initial_energy_demand_growth_rate)</eqn>
				<units>dmnl/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="initial energy\ndemand\ngrowth rate">
				<doc>${Internal Calibration Parameter}
</doc>
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>0.02</eqn>
				<range min="0" max="0.1"/>
				<units>dmnl/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="energy market\nbalance">
				<doc>It measures whether energy demand is growing faster or slower than energy supply.
If demand grows faster than supply → energy becomes scarce, price pressure upward. If supply grows faster than demand → energy becomes abundant, downward pressure on cost/ price.
</doc>
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>energy_demand_growth_rate[Run]-energy_supply_growth_rate[Run]</eqn>
				<units>dmnl/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="hyper inflation deflation stopper">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>IF Inflation_Rate &gt; 10 OR Inflation_Rate &lt; -10 THEN
5/0
ELSE
0</eqn>
				<units>dmnl</units>
			</aux>
		</variables>
